  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kokand Fertilisers GET Capex</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project will finance the implementation of an energy-efficiency oriented  CAPEX program at the recently privatised chemical plant Indorama Kokand  Fertilisers and Chemicals in Uzbekistan, as well as its initial working capital  needs. The WC Loan will be provided in local currency (&quot;UZS&quot;). Total EBRD  financing is USD 22.5 million. The Capex Loan (62% GET) is to be used to  finance the modernisation of the plant whereas the WC Loan will be used to  finance working capital related requirements. The Loans will be provided  together with the IFC who will lend alongside EBRD for the CAPEX portion of the  investment program. Corporate guarantee from the Sponsor for the entire  lifetime of the loans is secured.</narrative>
  </description>
